column2: What operating system do you use on the laptop you will bring to the workshops?
column3: Using R, could you import data from a spreadsheet and use a function to tell you number of observations (rows) and variables (columns) the data set contains?
column4: Using R, could you import data from a spreadsheet and subset specific rows and columns from the data and assign them to a new object?
column5: Using R, could you import data from a spreadsheet, select two variables, and then create a plot of points to explore the relationship between these variables on an x-y axis?
column6: Using R, could you import data from a spreadsheet and create a new variable (column) as a function of the existing variables? For example create a new column in the table containing the mean value of three other columns?
column7: Would you be able to export tabular data in R to a spreadsheet, for example a csv or excel file?
